## Stack

| Layer     | Technology                                             |
| --------- | ------------------------------------------------------ |
| Backend   | PHP {{PHP_VERSION}}, Laravel + Octane (Swoole)         |
| Frontend  | Vue 3 + AdminLTE, built with Vite (Node {{NODE_VERSION}}) |
| Database  | MySQL 8 (Docker service `mysql`)                       |
| Cache     | Redis (Docker service `redis`)                         |
| Packages  | csgt/utils, csgt/crud, csgt/cancerbero, csgt/menu      |
| Infra     | Docker Compose (`app`, `redis`, `mysql`)               |

## Local setup

Requirements: Docker Desktop (or Engine + Compose), git and Node {{NODE_VERSION}} on the host. Everything PHP runs inside the containers.

```bash
git clone git@github.com:{{REPO_SLUG}}.git
cd {{PROJECT_NAME}}
cp .env.example .env && cp docker-compose.yml.example docker-compose.yml
docker compose up -d --build
docker compose exec app composer install
docker compose exec app php artisan key:generate
docker compose exec app php artisan migrate
docker compose exec app php artisan db:seed --force
npm install
npm run dev
```

The app is served at `http://localhost` and the Vite dev server at port `5173`. `APP_ENV=production` by default in `.env`, so destructive Artisan commands (`migrate`, `db:seed`) require `--force`; set `APP_ENV=local` for local work.

