## Frequent commands

All PHP commands run inside the `app` container; frontend commands run on the host. The container shell ships aliases: `migrate`, `rollback`, `seed`, `seedgod` (= `db:seed --class=GodSeeder`), `cda` (= `composer dump-autoload`).

| Action              | Command                                              |
| ------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------- |
| Artisan             | `docker compose exec app php artisan <command>`      |
| Tests               | `docker compose exec app php artisan test`           |
| Single test         | `docker compose exec app php artisan test --filter=TestName` |
| Code style          | `docker compose exec app vendor/bin/pint`            |
| Logs                | `docker compose exec app php artisan pail`           |
| Frontend dev server | `npm run dev` (host)                                 |
| Production build    | `npm run build` (host)                               |
| Container shell     | `docker compose exec app bash`                       |

## CI/CD

The pipeline lives at `.github/workflows/ci.yml` (generated with `php artisan make:csgtci`). Every push and pull request runs code style, tests and the frontend build; pushes to the default branch additionally deploy to production when CI passes. The required repository secrets (`PRODUCTION_HOST`, `PRODUCTION_USER`, `PRODUCTION_PATH`, `PRODUCTION_SSH_KEY`, optional `PRODUCTION_SSH_PORT`, `PRODUCTION_SSH_KNOWN_HOSTS`, `PRODUCTION_HEALTHCHECK_URL`) are documented in the workflow itself.

